      <div class="leaders pull-left">
        <a href="#" target="new"><%= image_tag("team_creative/dan_granick.jpg",:class=>"displayed") %></a>
        <h5>Dan Granick, <br>President and CEO</h5>
        <p>Dan is our Team Leader! As President and owner of Creative, Dan has been in the industry for 22 years. He carries with him our master’s secrets and passion that were handed down to him from Stu Granick, Creative’s founder and inspiration. Dan thrives on the creative aspect of a promotion… always working on and planning the next great idea. <br>

        Majoring in advertising at the University of Illinois, Dan furthered his education and obtained his J.D. from IIT Chicago Kent College of Law. He practiced law as a corporate, business, estate planning and real estate attorney until he joined forces with Stu. Dan’s creativity and analytical skills have helped Creative become who we are today.<br>

        Dan is a friend to all who know him. He is always there for you whether it is business or personal. When he is not thinking about the next big thing he spends his time with his lovely wife of 25 years Joyce and his three beautiful daughters Melissa, Jessica and Jamie. </p>
      </div>
      <div class="leaders pull-left">
        <a href="#" target="new"><%= image_tag("team_creative/mike_elowe.jpg",:class=>"displayed") %></a>
        <h5>Michael Elowe, <br>Vice President</h5>
        <p>Mike is our lead operator. As Vice President and COO, Mike is all about getting things
        done! With 15 years of industry experience, Mike is responsible for planning Creative’s strategy and growth as well as lead client contact on a number of accounts. Mike graduated from the University of Illinois with a degree in finance. Feeling the need for more school, Mike then obtained his J.D. from UCLA School of Law. Mike practiced real estate and corporate law for almost ten years before joining Team Creative. When away from the office, Mike likes to spend time with his family and of course their dog, Louie. Mike enjoys golfing, skiing and keeping in shape whether swimming, cycling or running.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="leaders pull-left">
        <a href="#" target="new"><%= image_tag("team_creative/judy_elowe.jpg",:class=>"displayed") %></a>
        <h5>Judy Elowe, <br>Vice President</h5>
        <p>Judy specializes in exciting people about promotional products and branding solutions. As a Vice President at Creative, Judy has the opportunity to oversee the company’s business strategies in addition to interacting with customers on a daily basis. She works with Team Creative to ensure that her customers are getting the most creative ideas and the best customer service in the industry. <br>
        A graduate of the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign with a Business Administration and Marketing degree challenged her to start her first career working for a pharmaceutical company. After 8 years of sales, sales training, and management, Judy started her second career and joined her family’s business, Creative. It is at Creative that Judy is able to help customers integrate effective promotional marketing and branding solutions. Judy enjoys the long-standing relationships that she has developed over the past 18 years with her customers. She believes that no problem is too difficult to solve. And, it is often through her problem solving strategies that incredible positive outcomes are attained.<br>
        When she’s not thinking about the next customer project on her to do list, you can find Judy serving on the board of EPWNG (Exclusive Professional Networking Group), attending numerous networking meetings, exercising, grocery shopping and cooking and happily having a great cup of coffee. She lives in Northbrook, IL with her husband, two teenage children (although her daughter just left for her first year of college) and her adorable Puggle, Louie.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="leaders pull-left">
        <a href="#" target="new"><%= image_tag("team_creative/ann_bacigalupo.png",:class=>"displayed") %></a>
        <h5>Ann Bacigalupo, <br>Vice President</h5>
        <p>Ann stumbled upon the Promotional Products industry, while on an interview for customer service in 1985 in Nashville, TN. In 1988, when she moved back to her native Chicagoland, she stumbled upon Stu Granick and 3 years later Dan Granick joined the picture. In 1995, Ann
        helped Dan and Stu launch Creative Promotional Products and most days she loves her job. She says, her training as a first grade teacher helps her deal with sales people and the Creative brainstorming session are the highlights of her days. After hours, she spends with her partner Barb and their two dogs Tillie &amp; Tucker. She loves surfing the internet and one of her favorite sites is Stumble Upon!</p>
      </div>
